# CTPF vault operations

The vault is the program SSOT. Do not invent a parallel roadmap, `Handoff.md`, or second
next-steps file in the repo or vault.

## Before CTPF work

Read, in order:

1. `C:\Users\richs\vaults\MLSecOps Lab\CTPF\Project Instructions.md` (mode card)
2. The active plan named there (currently `CTPF/Plans/CTPF Agent-Operable Harness Plan.md`)
3. Doing/Next on `CTPF/Boards/Build.md` and `CTPF/Boards/Research.md`
4. Optionally lab-root `C:\Users\richs\vaults\MLSecOps Lab\Project-Status.md`

Verify claims against Git/`main` when sequence or repository state is asserted.

## Vault maintenance

- Work in plan/approve mode for vault edits and repo edits.
- After an approved gate, merge, or sequence change: update the active plan status and the
  Build/Research boards (move cards, refresh Doing/Next).
- Update `Project-Status.md` only on milestones or when it is clearly stale versus the plan/boards.
- Keep research findings, run evidence, session logs, evidence bundles, analysis notes, and
  publication drafts in the vault — never in this repository.

## Do not

- Copy private charter, evidence, or unpublished research into the repo
- Paste full vault plans into `AGENTS.md` or other repo docs
- Resume archived Act I / pre-salvage boards without explicit instruction
